Flow CMS — License
===================

Flow CMS is open-core. This repository contains two differently-licensed parts.

1. Open-source core
-------------------
Everything EXCEPT `apps/api/src/ee/` (the studio, the headless API, content
modeling, the delivery APIs, auth/RBAC, the AI + SEO suites, media, webhooks,
importers, CLI, SDK, and all packages) is free and open source.

Intended license: Apache-2.0 (permissive, with an explicit patent grant).

  NOTE: The exact open-source license is pending final confirmation by the
  project owner. Until the verbatim license text is committed here, treat the
  core as "source-available, intended Apache-2.0" and contact the vendor for any
  use beyond evaluation. Candidate licenses and trade-offs are discussed in
  `docs/business/LICENSING.md` and `docs/business/MONETIZATION.md`.

2. Commercial (Enterprise Edition)
----------------------------------
Everything under `apps/api/src/ee/` is commercial, proprietary code, governed by
`apps/api/src/ee/LICENSE` — NOT by the open-source license above. It may be used
only with a valid Flow CMS commercial license (Pro / Enterprise) and is unlocked
at runtime by an Ed25519-signed license key.

Full details: `docs/business/LICENSING.md`.
